[assistant] - Public ElGamal key APIs in this artifact create `org.bouncycastle.jcajce.provider.asymmetric.elgamal.BCElGamalPrivateKey`, not `JCEElGamalPrivateKey`.
[assistant] - The only natural path to `JCEElGamalPrivateKey.readObject(...)` / `writeObject(...)` is Java serialization of an existing `JCEElGamalPrivateKey`.
[assistant] - A crafted serialization test can reach those methods on the JVM, but it fails under Native Image with missing serialization/reflection metadata before entering `readObject(...)`.
[assistant] - The dynamic-access report records this class as `Unknown Source` with no line numbers, and the coverage implementation only marks dynamic-access call sites covered when a reported source line is covered. Even when JaCoCo shows the private `readObject`/`writeObject` methods executed, the dynamic-access call sites remain uncovered because there is no line number to match.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Because the remaining paths require either unsupported test-side stream fabrication plus missing Native Image metadata, direct reflection/unsafe access, or shadowing library classes, I left the active class uncovered rather than adding a brittle or non-supported test. I also removed the previously added `JCEElGamalPrivateKeyTest.java` so it does not introduce Native Image failures.
